## Step 1: Multiply the first row of the first matrix by the column of the second matrix
$\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 2 \\ 4 & 8 \\ \end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 1*5 + 2*3 \\ 4*5 + 8*3 \\ \end{pmatrix}$
## Step 2: Perform the arithmetic operations in the first row
$\begin{pmatrix} 1*5 + 2*3 \\ 4*5 + 8*3 \\ \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 5 + 6 \\ 20 + 24 \\ \end{pmatrix}$
## Step 3: Perform the arithmetic operations in the second row
$\begin{pmatrix} 5 + 6 \\ 20 + 24 \\ \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 11 \\ 44 \\ \end{pmatrix}$
## Step 4: $\begin{pmatrix} 11 \\ 44 \\ \end{pmatrix}$
